# Setup rc statup script for alpine linux
alpine linux is a great lightweight linus distribution to run web servers on.  Use the below steps to create a rc startup script to startup your tunnels easily:

## Steps:

 1. Install loclx on the system and cp it to /usr/local/sbin
     cp loclx /usr/local/sbin
     chmod 755 /usr/local/sbin/loclx
2. Create a /etc/localexpose directory and put the config.yaml file there.  The following will create an example [config.yaml](https://localxpose.io/docs/cli/config.yaml)

    # mkdir /etc/localxpose
    # chmod 750 /etc/localxpose
    # cat > /etc/localxpose/config.yaml << EOF
    webexample:
      type: http
      region: us
      reserved_domain: www.example.com
      to: localhost:8080
      plugins:
        https_redirect: true
        request_header:
          - host:www.example.com
          - X-Token:secureToken
    minecraft:
      type: udp
      region: us
      reserved_endpoint: us.loclx.io:31969
      to: 10.0.112.9:19132


    # cp loclx /usr/local/sbin
    # chmod 755 /usr/local/sbin/loclx
    # mkdir /etc/localxpose
    # cat > /etc/localxpose/config.yaml << EOF
